01/08/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- State Minister for Foreign Trade Kursat Tuzmen said late on Wednesday (30 July) that Turkish firms have been awarded $90m in contracts in Iraq's construction sector.
A group of 40 Iraqi businessmen were expected in Ankara for further talks, he told members of the local business community.
Tuzmen promised that a measure would be adopted to increase traffic across the Habur border checkpoint, adding that the railway link between Turkey and Iraq would open soon.
(AFP - 31/07/03)
